When an opportunity comes along,
grab it.

233
00:16:02,632 --> 00:16:06,227
- What about the age thing?
- What about it?

234
00:16:06,556 --> 00:16:11,152
You see an old man in the street
with a young girl, what do you think?

235
00:16:11,524 --> 00:16:14,243
I think he must be really rich.

236
00:16:15,991 --> 00:16:19,461
- Then i try to make eye contact.
- Ah.

237
00:16:25,511 --> 00:16:28,548
There you are, frasier.
I'm so glad you called me.

238
00:16:28,850 --> 00:16:31,045
Thanks for coming.

239
00:16:31,856 --> 00:16:36,247
Maris's friends introduced me to
a party game i'd like to share with you...

240
00:16:36,616 --> 00:16:39,574
- i'd really like to talk.
- This first. It's a hoot.

241
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:43,847
If you were on a desert island
with one meal,

242
00:16:44,131 --> 00:16:46,770
one aria and one bottle of wine,
what would they be?

243
00:16:47,053 --> 00:16:49,362
- Niles, i really...
- frasier.

244
00:16:49,642 --> 00:16:51,678
Ok.

245
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:55,609
A big mac,
"i'm your venus" and ripple.

246
00:16:58,660 --> 00:17:01,857
If you're going to mock the game,
don't play.

247
00:17:02,167 --> 00:17:06,160
- Gladly.
- Are you still cramped up about age?

248
00:17:06,508 --> 00:17:09,227
No, i'm fine. By the way, you were right.

249
00:17:09,514 --> 00:17:11,550
Oh, i love to hear that.

250
00:17:11,811 --> 00:17:16,441
Yes, but i do have a problem.
The other day i was asked out by, er,

251
00:17:16,821 --> 00:17:19,494
this 22-year-old girl
that i met in the mall.

252
00:17:19,786 --> 00:17:22,175
- That is alarming.
- I turned her down.

253
00:17:22,457 --> 00:17:24,812
In a mall? Did anyone see you?

254
00:17:26,131 --> 00:17:29,043
Niles. I'm just wondering
if i made the right decision.

255
00:17:29,346 --> 00:17:33,385
I would love to go out with this girl.
She's fantastic.

256
00:17:33,730 --> 00:17:37,882
But i could look like some old fool
chasing after a young girl,

257
00:17:38,239 --> 00:17:41,868
becoming a walking midlife crisis cliché,

258
00:17:42,205 --> 00:17:45,436
running around
like that buffoon stanley barrister.

259
00:17:45,754 --> 00:17:51,033
- Oh, that is embarrassing.
- That girl, how old can she be?

260
00:17:51,432 --> 00:17:53,468
- 21, if she's a day.
- Frightening!

261
00:17:53,728 --> 00:17:56,640
I saw them last tuesday night together.

262
00:17:56,943 --> 00:18:02,017
- I saw them wednesday morning.
- ew!

263
00:18:02,412 --> 00:18:06,530
- That's disgusting!
- People will say the same about me!

264
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:10,156
Stanley barrister is a 60-year-old man

265
00:18:10,470 --> 00:18:12,426
who wears a toupee
that looks like something

266
00:18:12,683 --> 00:18:14,958
he pulled out of a shower drain.

267
00:18:16,190 --> 00:18:19,580
You are 41
and obviously not wearing a toupee.

268
00:18:22,035 --> 00:18:23,991
Thank you, niles.

269
00:18:24,247 --> 00:18:27,557
- You think it's ok for me to date her?
- It doesn't matter.

270
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:31,236
- I value your opinion.
- It's irrelevant.

271
00:18:31,553 --> 00:18:34,625
Don't be coy,
and please stop pursing your lips.

272
00:18:34,936 --> 00:18:38,895
You look like one of those old women
they carve out of dried apples.

273
00:18:41,281 --> 00:18:47,754
Don't you see? What i think about you
dating a younger woman is immaterial.

274
00:18:48,212 --> 00:18:50,680
- What matters is what you think.
- Hm...

275
00:18:50,968 --> 00:18:54,438
would you be doing it
to run away from your age

276
00:18:54,767 --> 00:18:58,362
or because
this could become a relationship?

277
00:18:59,694 --> 00:19:02,254
- I don't know.
- Find out.

278
00:19:02,532 --> 00:19:05,649
- Then to hell with what people think.
- You are right.

279
00:19:05,956 --> 00:19:09,346
Oh! There it is again.
I never tire of hearing that.

280
00:19:09,672 --> 00:19:12,425
Let the tongues
of the doubting nabobs wag.

281
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:15,871
- If it feels right, make yourself happy.
- Thank you.

